olive oil
2 potato
1 bag herbs
1 bunch spring onion
2 radish
1 apple
1 tin black beans
1 packet Plant-Based Grated Cheese
¼ cup plain flour
2 tbs plant-based milk
1 bag salad leaves
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet Plant-Based Aioli
1 sachet Mexican Fiesta spice blend

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Cut potato into fries, then place on a lined oven
tray. Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and
toss to coat. Bake until tender, 20-25 minutes.

• Meanwhile, roughly chop herbs.
• Thinly slice spring onion, radish and apple.
• Drain black beans, reserving the liquid, then
rinse beans thoroughly.

• SPICY! You may find the spice blend hot! Add less
if you're sensitive to heat.
• In a medium bowl, combine black beans,
plant-based grated cheese, Mexican Fiesta
spice blend, herbs, spring onion, the plain
flour, plant-based milk, some reserved bean
liquid (3 tbs for 2 people / 1/4 cup for 4 people)
and a pinch of salt. Mix well to combine.

TIP: Lift out some of the mixture with a spoon. If it's
too wet and doesn't hold its shape, add a little
more flour!

• Heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat
with enough olive oil to coat the base.
• When oil is hot, add heaped tablespoons of
fritter mixture in batches and flatten with a
spatula (3-4 per person). Cook until golden,
3-4 minutes each side. Transfer to a paper
towel-lined plate.

TIP: Add extra olive oil between batches as needed.
Don’t flip before the time is up to ensure your fritters
can set.

• Meanwhile, combine salad leaves, apple, radish
and a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil
in a large bowl. Season with salt and pepper.

• Divide black bean and plant-based cheese
fritters, fries and salad between plates.
• Serve with plant-based aioli. Enjoy!